# ctsc editing rules

- This repo is a C port of TypeScript's compiler, driven by an agent harness.
  AGENTS.md is the source of truth; read it if you have not already.
- Only modify files under `ctsc/`. Never touch `harness/`, `upstream/`,
  `.cursor/`, or `fixtures/` unless the user explicitly asks you to.
- Behaviour must match `tsc` byte-for-byte. Positions are UTF-16 code units.
  `ts.SyntaxKind` names are verbatim.
- Before editing a phase, open the corresponding reference file under
  `upstream/TypeScript/src/compiler/` (scanner.ts / parser.ts / binder.ts /
  checker.ts / emitter.ts) and cite line numbers in your commit message.
- When adding a new `CtscSyntaxKind`, update BOTH `ctsc/include/ctsc/scanner.h`
  AND the name table in `ctsc/src/scanner/token_names.c` in the same edit.
- New behaviour needs a unit test under `ctsc/tests/`. Do not delete tests.
- After edits, the build (`cmake --build ctsc/build/default`) and the unit
  tests (`ctsc_tests`) must both pass.
- Keep the `core/` modules dependency-free (no malloc outside arena if
  avoidable, no third-party libs).
- Do NOT reformat files you did not otherwise modify.
